The country has 279 factories oriented to the domestic market and 17 to the external market. 14 processing industries were created that produced products such as guacamole, cellulose, fruit halves, frozen foods, drinks and crude oil. As a result of this activity, more than 40 000 direct jobs, about 70,000 seasonal jobs and over 180,000 indirect permanent jobs.[7]

The export potential of avocados is limited due to the properties of the product.[13] Exports more than quadrupled between 2000 and 2011, accounting for 27.45 percent of the total production of 12.64 million tons in 2011[4].